scopecontent.p:
These volumes contain individual service records for
         officers who served in the Virginia Volunteers or Virginia
         National Guard between 1871 and 1920. The service records
         provide the following information about the officers: Name;
         Command or Department; Elected or Appointed (date); Rank;
         Residence; Accepted (date); Examined by State Board (date);
         Result (passed or failed); Examined by Federal Board; Result
         (passed or failed); Date Federal Recognition; Date State
         Commission; Prior Service (years enlisted or years
         commissioned); Date Physical Exam; Result; Enlisted as (rank);
         Company, Battery, or Troop; Squadron, Battalion, or Regiment;
         Virginia Volunteers or National Guard and date; and blank
         spaces for dates appointed corporal, sergeant, detailed mess
         sergeant or supply sergeant, or q.m. sergeant, 1st sergeant,
         bn. sergeant-major, and regimental sergeant-major.
